## CEO ANSWERS (full text in KB entry 230)

1. **Transfers**: Both directions allowed. Personal→Org: user initiates, no collaborator consent. Org→Other: admin initiates, target accepts via one-time dashboard prompt. MANDATORY audit log (compliance, Baptist).
2. **Multi-org**: Yes. Per-user `default_org_id`. CLI uses default; `--org` flag overrides. Daemon routes by `project.org_id`.
3. **Member removal**: Revoke access, NEVER destroy data. Sessions stay (org owns byte trail). Projects auto-transfer to removing admin. KB entries stay with `authored_by` preserved.
4. **Deferred**: see "NOT in scope" above.

