### Phase 5 — Multi-org daemon routing
- THE LOAD-BEARING PIECE. Get this wrong and two-org users see sessions in the wrong bucket.
- Default-org: User.default_org_id read at daemon startup AND per-session capture.
- `sfs config set default-org <slug>` writes to `~/.sessionfs/config.toml`.
- `sfs project init` defaults to `default_org_id`. `--org <slug>` overrides. If user has multiple orgs and no default, CLI prompts.
- Daemon capture path: when a new session is detected, look up the corresponding `project.org_id` (via project lookup from workspace path or via tracked_sessions). Route the session's sync upload to that org's storage.
- For untracked workspaces (no project linked): use the user's default_org_id; if none, fall back to personal (org_id = null).
- Tests: 6 — daemon routing happy-path, default-org fallback, --org override, multi-org user with no default (prompt path), sync routing per session, daemon restart preserves routing.

DONE when: a user with two orgs (acme + beta) can start a session in an acme project and see the session land in acme's storage tier limits, not beta's.

