## RISKS & MITIGATIONS

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|
| Project transfer races (two users accept simultaneously) | Atomic UPDATE with WHERE state='pending', return affected_row_count; non-1 → 409 |
| Daemon routing for in-flight sessions during transfer | Hold transfer accept until current sync completes for the project; or just re-route next session (simpler — sessions are append-only, the transfer doesn't migrate historical data anyway) |
| Multi-org user with default_org_id pointing to an org they were removed from | Validate default_org_id on every load; null it on member-removal |
| Migration 035 backfill on large project tables | Trivial — adding a nullable column with no backfill is O(1) in PG; SQLite is fine at any scale we have |
| Compatibility with existing personal projects | `org_id = NULL` is the existing state; nothing changes for personal projects until user opts in |
| Audit log volume for transfers | Negligible (low-frequency event); log to existing `audit_log` table |

